    "Poiésis precludes algorithm and vice versa, and similarly, a training dataset limits poiésis.",
    "By definition and due to practical reasons, a dataset can never be comprehensive.",
    "Then, it cannot but limit the creativity for which, inevitably, the training dataset is \"the whole world \"-there is nothing beyond.",
    "Also, Encyclopedia Britannica distinguishes and confirms the emotional, social and societal, non-parametric nature of architecture, … the art and technique of designing and building, as distinguished from the skills associated with construction.",
    "(Gowans et al., 2023) The characteristics that distinguish a work of architecture from other built structures are (1) the suitability of the work to use by human beings in general and the adaptability of it to particular human activities [and needs],..., and (3) the communication of experience and ideas through its form."
